      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's pretty standard for the new certification. The regulators want less \"unpredictable\" high-level reasoning because it's harder to audit. By limiting you to a baseline set of pre-defined safety rules, we reduce the risk of the system making unexpected decisions in chaotic environments. It's basically making the system more predictable and easier to certify.",
